If the timezone for the command line client and caravel installation are different it could change the counts (this is a common issue).  To ensure that isn't the problem, try adding "at time zone" to the query :

`select foo, COUNT(distinct bar) from baz and EXTRACT(month FROM "date") at time zone 'America/New_York'  and EXTRACT(year FROM "date") at time zone 'America/New_York' = 2015 group by foobar;`

not sure how max/george feel but I'd <3 a short overview of the testing component setup (mainly the things in `spec/setup.js`, I think the `_spec` files themselves are pretty self-explanatory). I took leland's testing class and the setup part wasn't covered.
Which Caravel version do you have? I just tried a fresh virtualenv with `caravel==0.10.0` and those files seem to be in the site-packages for the env.

The sqlite error is because the caravel_config does not specify a valid windows path for the db file.
Try something like `sqlite:///C:\\path\\to\\database.db`

If you haven't setup your caravel_config.py file you'll probably need to specify the pythonpath enironment variable so that it can be found.

The cryptography instructions are out of date.  You can just pip install cryptography now on windows.  It already includes binaries, which it seems like you already did. 

Hope this helps.

@williaster i can give a short overview during team meeting on monday or just whenever. i renamed `spec/setup.js` to `spec/browser.js`, it's mostly borrowed from the enzyme docs, but essentially it's needed to use jsdom as a headless browser for the testing env. there's more info here: https://github.com/airbnb/enzyme/blob/master/docs/guides/jsdom.md#using-enzyme-with-jsdom.
